{"questionId":"3017658","questionHtml":"<p>Given that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>L</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></math> is an AS-linear function, show that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>L</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>m</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>m</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mrow><mi>m</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p>attempts to use <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi>d</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>)</mo><mi>r</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>m</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>c</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>r</mi></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>(M1)</strong> </em>for attempting to use <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi>d</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>)</mo><mi>m</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>r</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>r</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>c</mi></math>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi>d</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>)</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi>c</mi><mi>m</mi></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mi>m</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>c</mi><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi>c</mi><mi>m</mi></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi>d</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>)</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi>c</mi><mi>m</mi></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mi>m</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>c</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>m</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>removes the denominator <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>m</mi></math> from their expression involving <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>m</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>m</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi><mi>m</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math> (or equivalent)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>attempts to use <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>m</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi>r</mi></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>m</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>c</mi></mrow><mi>m</mi></mfrac></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>removes the denominator <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>m</mi></math> from their expression involving <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>m</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>m</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi><mi>m</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math> (or equivalent)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>attempts to use&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>m</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>d</mi></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>m</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi>c</mi><mi>m</mi></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mi>m</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>m</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mrow><mi>c</mi><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi>c</mi><mi>m</mi></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfenced></math>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>removes the denominator <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>m</mi></math> from their expression involving <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>m</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>m</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi><mi>m</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math> (or equivalent)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>attempts to use <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>m</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>d</mi></math> and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>m</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>d</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>m</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>(</mo><mi>r</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>m</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>)</mo></math> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>m</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>d</mi><mi>m</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>m</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>d</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math> &nbsp;(or equivalent) &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>substitutes&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>d</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>c</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>m</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math> into their expression involving <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>m</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>d</mi></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>m</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi><mi>m</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math> (or equivalent)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>m</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>m</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>⇒</mo><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>m</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mrow><mi>m</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac></math> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for a convincing demonstration that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>m</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mrow><mi>m</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac></math>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>so <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>L</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>m</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>m</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mrow><mi>m</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac></math> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Do not accept working backwards from the <em><strong>AG</strong></em>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2</strong></p>\n<p>considers <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>L</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>m</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>m</mi><mi>r</mi></math></p>\n<p>attempts to use&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi>d</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>)</mo><mi>r</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>m</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>c</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>r</mi></math> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em> for attempting to use <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi>d</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>)</mo><mi>m</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>r</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>r</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>c</mi></math>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi>d</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>)</mo><mi>r</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>m</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mi>m</mi><mi>r</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>r</mi></math> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempts to express <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi></math> in terms of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>m</mi></math> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi>r</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>m</mi><mi>r</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>m</mi><mo>⇒</mo><mi>r</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>m</mi><mrow><mi>m</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac></math> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>so <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>L</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>m</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>m</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mrow><mi>m</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac></math> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Do not accept working backwards from the <em><strong>AG</strong></em>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[4 marks]</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","meta":{"questionId":"3017658","referenceCode":"23M.3.AHL.TZ2.2bii","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Given that L(x) is an AS-linear function, show that L(x)=mx-m2m+2.","paper":"3","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Numbe